By Aisha Cole Lagos – The Nigerian Ports Authority (NPA) says 25 ships laden with petroleum products, food and other goods will berth at Apapa and Tin Can Island Ports between Thursday and May 24. The NPA made this known in its daily publications, ‘Shipping Position’. It said that four of the ships would sail in with petrol. It added that the other 21 ships
would bring in general cargo, bulk sugar, bulk fertiliser, frozen fish,
buckwheat, bitumen and containers carrying different goods. It also stated that 16 ships had
arrived at the ports earlier, waiting to berth with frozen fish, general
cargo, aviation fuel, containers and petrol.